  "prompt": "What is love when there is nobody to love?",
  "response": "That's a profound philosophical and emotional question. Love can exist even without a specific recipient:\n\n1. Self-love - Caring for oneself, nurturing inner peace and personal growth\n\n2. Potential love - The capacity to love, which remains within you even when not actively expressed\n\n3. Universal love - Compassion for humanity, kindness towards all beings\n\n4. Abstract love - Love as an idea, an energy that transcends individual relationships\n\n5. Spiritual love - Connection to a higher principle or universal consciousness\n\nLove isn't just about having someone to love, but about the ability to love itself. It's a state of being, an openness to connection and empathy, even in solitude.\n\nWould you like to explore this idea further?",
